◆ CheckDimensions()

void BrawlCrate.UI.Model_Previewer.ModelEditControl.ModelEditControl.CheckDimensions ( )
inline
119 {
120 int totalWidth = animEditors.Width;
121 Size s = new Size(animCtrlPnl.Width, animEditors.Height);
122 if (_currentControl != null && _currentControl.Visible)
123 {
124 s = _currentControl.Visible ? _currentControl is SCN0Editor ? scn0Editor.GetDimensions() :
125 _currentControl.MinimumSize :
126 !weightEditor.Visible && !vertexEditor.Visible ? new Size(0, 0) : s;
127 }
128 else if (!weightEditor.Visible && !vertexEditor.Visible)
129 {
130 s = new Size(0, 0);
131 }
132 else if (weightEditor.Visible)
133 {
134 s = weightEditor.MinimumSize;
135 }
136 else if (vertexEditor.Visible)
137 {
138 s = vertexEditor.MinimumSize;
139 }
140
141 //See if the scroll bar needs to be visible
142 int addedHeight = 0;
143 if (s.Width + pnlPlayback.MinimumSize.Width > totalWidth)
144 {
145 addedHeight = 17;
146 animEditors.HorizontalScroll.Visible = true;
147 }
148 else
149 {
150 animEditors.HorizontalScroll.Visible = false;
151 }
152
153
154 animCtrlPnl.Width = s.Width;
155 animEditors.Height = s.Height + addedHeight;
156
157 //Dock playback panel if it reaches its minimum size
158 if (pnlPlayback.Width <= pnlPlayback.MinimumSize.Width)
159 {
160 pnlPlayback.Dock = DockStyle.Left;
161 pnlPlayback.Width = pnlPlayback.MinimumSize.Width;
162 }
163 else
164 {
165 pnlPlayback.Dock = DockStyle.Fill;
166 }
167
168 //Stretch playback panel if there's space
169 if (animEditors.Width - animCtrlPnl.Width >= pnlPlayback.MinimumSize.Width)
170 {
171 pnlPlayback.Width += animEditors.Width - animCtrlPnl.Width - pnlPlayback.MinimumSize.Width;
172 pnlPlayback.Dock = DockStyle.Fill;
173 }
174 else
175 {
176 pnlPlayback.Dock = DockStyle.Left;
177 }
178 }

inlineprivate
497 {
498 IModel m = TargetModel;
499 _updating = true;
500 foreach (IModel node in _targetModels)
501 {

503 {
504 ModelPanel.RemoveTarget(node);
505 }

507
508 List<CollisionNode> newCollisions = new List<CollisionNode>();

516 newColl.AddChild(o);

◆ leftToolStripMenuItem1_Click()

void BrawlCrate.UI.Model_Previewer.ModelEditControl.ModelEditControl.leftToolStripMenuItem1_Click ( object  sender,
EventArgs  e 
)
inlineprivate
355 {
356 ModelPanelViewport curViewport = modelPanel.CurrentViewport;
357 ModelPanelViewport newViewport = ModelPanelViewport.DefaultPerspective;
358 newViewport.BackgroundColor = curViewport.BackgroundColor;
359 ModelPanel.AddViewport(newViewport);
360
361 float xMin = curViewport.Percentages._x;
362 float yMin = curViewport.Percentages._y;
363 float xMax = curViewport.Percentages._z;
364 float yMax = curViewport.Percentages._w;
365 float averageX = (xMin + xMax) / 2.0f;
366
367 curViewport.SetPercentages(averageX, yMin, xMax, yMax);
368 newViewport.SetPercentages(xMin, yMin, averageX, yMax);
369
370 ModelPanel.Invalidate();
371 }

◆ PointCollides() [2/2]

bool BrawlCrate.UI.Model_Previewer.ModelEditControl.ModelEditControl.PointCollides ( Vector3  point,
out float  y_result 
)
inlineprivate
575 {
576 y_result = float.MaxValue;
577 Vector2 v2 = new Vector2(point._x, point._y);
578 foreach (CollisionNode coll in _collisions)
579 {
580 foreach (CollisionObject obj in coll.Children)
581 {
582 if (obj._render)
583 {
584 foreach (CollisionPlane plane in obj._planes)
585 {
586 if (plane._type == CollisionPlaneType.Floor && plane.IsCharacters)
587 {
588 if (plane.PointLeft._x <= v2._x && plane.PointRight._x >= v2._x)
589 {
590 float x = v2._x;
591 float m = (plane.PointLeft._y - plane.PointRight._y)
592 / (plane.PointLeft._x - plane.PointRight._x);
593 float b = plane.PointRight._y - m * plane.PointRight._x;
594 float y_target = m * x + b;
595 //Console.WriteLine(y_target);
596 if (Math.Abs(y_target - v2._y) <= Math.Abs(y_result - v2._y))
597 {
598 y_result = y_target;
599 }
600 }
601 }
602 }
603 }
604 }
605 }
606
607 return Math.Abs(y_result - v2._y) <= 5;
608 }

◆ RenderBrawlStageData()

void BrawlCrate.UI.Model_Previewer.ModelEditControl.ModelEditControl.RenderBrawlStageData ( ModelPanelViewport  panel)
inline
21 {
22 //If you ever make changes to GL attributes (enabled and disabled things)
23 //and don't want to keep track of what you changed,
24 //you can push all attributes and then pop them when you're done, like this.
25 //This will make sure the GL state is back to how it was before you changed it.
26 GL.PushAttrib(AttribMask.AllAttribBits);
27
28 GL.Disable(EnableCap.DepthTest);
29
30 if (RenderCollisions)
31 {
32 foreach (CollisionNode node in _collisions)
33 {
34 node.Render();
35 }
36 }
37
38 #region RenderOverlays
39
40 List<MDL0BoneNode> ItemBones = new List<MDL0BoneNode>();
41
42 MDL0Node stgPos = null;
43
44 MDL0BoneNode CamBone0 = null,
45 CamBone1 = null,
46 DeathBone0 = null,
47 DeathBone1 = null;
48
49 //Get bones and render spawns if checked
50 if (_targetModel != null &&
51 _targetModel is MDL0Node &&
52 (((ResourceNode) _targetModel).Name.Contains("StgPosition") ||
53 ((ResourceNode) _targetModel).Name.Contains("stagePosition")))
54 {
55 stgPos = _targetModel as MDL0Node;
56 }
57 else if (_targetModels != null)
58 {
59 stgPos = _targetModels.Find(x => x is MDL0Node &&
60 ((ResourceNode) x).Name.Contains("StgPosition") ||
61 ((ResourceNode) x).Name.Contains("stagePosition")) as MDL0Node;
62 }
63
64 if (stgPos != null)
65 {
66 foreach (MDL0BoneNode bone in stgPos._linker.BoneCache)
67 {
68 if (bone._name == "CamLimit0N")
69 {
70 CamBone0 = bone;
71 }
72 else if (bone.Name == "CamLimit1N")
73 {
74 CamBone1 = bone;
75 }
76 else if (bone.Name == "Dead0N")
77 {
78 DeathBone0 = bone;
79 }
80 else if (bone.Name == "Dead1N")
81 {
82 DeathBone1 = bone;
83 }
84 else if (bone._name.StartsWith("Player") && bone._name.Length == 8 && chkSpawns.Checked)
85 {
86 Vector3 position = bone._frameMatrix.GetPoint();
87 if (PointCollides(position))
88 {
89 GL.Color4(0.0f, 1.0f, 0.0f, 0.5f);
90 }
91 else
92 {
93 GL.Color4(1.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f, 0.5f);
94 }
95
96 TKContext.DrawSphere(position, 5.0f, 32);
97 if (int.TryParse(bone._name.Substring(6, 1), out int playernum))
98 {
99 panel.NoSettingsScreenText[playernum.ToString()] =
100 panel.Camera.Project(position) - new Vector3(8.0f, 8.0f, 0);
101 }
102 }
103 else if (bone._name.StartsWith("Rebirth") && bone._name.Length == 9 && chkSpawns.Checked)
104 {
105 GL.Color4(1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f, 0.1f);
106 TKContext.DrawSphere(bone._frameMatrix.GetPoint(), 5.0f, 32);
107 if (int.TryParse(bone._name.Substring(7, 1), out int playernum))
108 {
109 panel.NoSettingsScreenText[playernum.ToString()] =
110 panel.Camera.Project(bone._frameMatrix.GetPoint()) - new Vector3(8.0f, 8.0f, 0);
111 }
112 }
113 else if (bone._name.StartsWith("Item"))
114 {
115 ItemBones.Add(bone);
116 }
117 }
118 }
119
120 //Render item fields if checked
121 if (ItemBones != null && chkItems.Checked)
122 {
123 GL.Color4(0.5f, 0.0f, 1.0f, 0.4f);
124 for (int i = 0; i < ItemBones.Count; i += 2)
125 {
126 Vector3 pos1, pos2;
127 if (ItemBones[i]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._y == ItemBones[i + 1]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._y)
128 {
129 pos1 = new Vector3(ItemBones[i]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._x,
130 ItemBones[i]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._y + 1.5f, 1.0f);
131 pos2 = new Vector3(ItemBones[i + 1]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._x,
132 ItemBones[i + 1]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._y - 1.5f, 1.0f);
133 }
134 else
135 {
136 pos1 = new Vector3(ItemBones[i]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._x,
137 ItemBones[i]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._y, 1.0f);
138 pos2 = new Vector3(ItemBones[i + 1]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._x,
139 ItemBones[i + 1]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._y, 1.0f);
140 }
141
142
143 if (pos1._x != pos2._x)
144 {
145 TKContext.DrawBox(pos1, pos2);
146 }
147 else
148 {
149 TKContext.DrawSphere(
150 new Vector3(ItemBones[i]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._x,
151 ItemBones[i]._frameMatrix.GetPoint()._y, pos1._z), 3.0f, 32);
152 }
153 }
154 }
155
156 //Render boundaries if checked
157 if (CamBone0 != null && CamBone1 != null && chkBoundaries.Checked)
158 {
159 //GL.Clear(ClearBufferMask.DepthBufferBit);
160 GL.Disable(EnableCap.DepthTest);
161 GL.Disable(EnableCap.Lighting);
162 GL.PolygonMode(MaterialFace.FrontAndBack, PolygonMode.Fill);
163 GL.Enable(EnableCap.CullFace);
164 GL.CullFace(CullFaceMode.Front);
165
166 GL.Color4(Color.Blue);
167 GL.Begin(BeginMode.LineLoop);
168 GL.LineWidth(15.0f);
169
170 Vector3
171 camBone0 = CamBone0._frameMatrix.GetPoint(),
172 camBone1 = CamBone1._frameMatrix.GetPoint(),
173 deathBone0 = DeathBone0._frameMatrix.GetPoint(),
174 deathBone1 = DeathBone1._frameMatrix.GetPoint();
175
176 GL.Vertex2(camBone0._x, camBone0._y);
177 GL.Vertex2(camBone1._x, camBone0._y);
178 GL.Vertex2(camBone1._x, camBone1._y);
179 GL.Vertex2(camBone0._x, camBone1._y);
180 GL.End();
181 GL.Begin(BeginMode.LineLoop);
182 GL.Color4(Color.Red);
183 GL.Vertex2(deathBone0._x, deathBone0._y);
184 GL.Vertex2(deathBone1._x, deathBone0._y);
185 GL.Vertex2(deathBone1._x, deathBone1._y);
186 GL.Vertex2(deathBone0._x, deathBone1._y);
187 GL.End();
188 GL.Color4(0.0f, 0.5f, 1.0f, 0.3f);
189 GL.Begin(BeginMode.TriangleFan);
190 GL.Vertex2(camBone0._x, camBone0._y);
191 GL.Vertex2(deathBone0._x, deathBone0._y);
192 GL.Vertex2(deathBone1._x, deathBone0._y);
193 GL.Vertex2(camBone1._x, camBone0._y);
194 GL.End();
195 GL.Begin(BeginMode.TriangleFan);
196 GL.Vertex2(camBone1._x, camBone1._y);
197 GL.Vertex2(deathBone1._x, deathBone1._y);
198 GL.Vertex2(deathBone0._x, deathBone1._y);
199 GL.Vertex2(camBone0._x, camBone1._y);
200 GL.End();
201 GL.Begin(BeginMode.TriangleFan);
202 GL.Vertex2(camBone1._x, camBone0._y);
203 GL.Vertex2(deathBone1._x, deathBone0._y);
204 GL.Vertex2(deathBone1._x, deathBone1._y);
205 GL.Vertex2(camBone1._x, camBone1._y);
206 GL.End();
207 GL.Begin(BeginMode.TriangleFan);
208 GL.Vertex2(camBone0._x, camBone1._y);
209 GL.Vertex2(deathBone0._x, deathBone1._y);
210 GL.Vertex2(deathBone0._x, deathBone0._y);
211 GL.Vertex2(camBone0._x, camBone0._y);
212 GL.End();
213 }
214
215 #endregion
216
217 GL.PopAttrib();
218 }

649 {

◆ SelectedPolygonChanged()

void BrawlCrate.UI.Model_Previewer.ModelEditControl.ModelEditControl.SelectedPolygonChanged ( )
inline
940 {
941 //We can't return here if the selected polygon is set to null.
942 //If the target model is changed or the selected object is cleared,
943 //things relying on the selected object must be updated to reflect that.
944 //if (leftPanel.SelectedPolygon == null) return;
945
946 //This sets the selected object index internally in the model.
947 //This determines the target object for focus editing vertices, normals, etc in the viewer
948 //If the selected object is set to null, the poly index will be set to -1 by IndexOf.
949 //This means vertices, normals etc will be drawn for all objects, if enabled.
950 _targetModel.SelectedObjectIndex = _targetModel.Objects.IndexOf(leftPanel.SelectedObject);
951
952 //If this setting is enabled, we need to show the user what textures only this object uses.
953 //If the polygon is set to null, all of the model's texture references will be shown.
954 if (SyncTexturesToObjectList)
955 {
956 leftPanel.UpdateTextures();
957 }
958
959 //Update the VIS editor to show the entries for the selected object
960 if (TargetAnimType == NW4RAnimType.VIS &&
961 leftPanel.SelectedObject != null &&
962 vis0Editor.listBox1.Items.Count != 0 &&
963 leftPanel.SelectedObject is MDL0ObjectNode)
964 {
965 MDL0ObjectNode o = (MDL0ObjectNode) leftPanel.SelectedObject;
966
967 int x = 0;
968 foreach (object i in vis0Editor.listBox1.Items)
969 {
970 if (o._drawCalls.Count > 0 && i.ToString() == o._drawCalls[0].VisibilityBone)
971 {
972 vis0Editor.listBox1.SelectedIndex = x;
973 break;
974 }
975
976 x++;
977 }
978
979 if (x == vis0Editor.listBox1.Items.Count)
980 {
981 vis0Editor.listBox1.SelectedIndex = -1;
982 }
983 }
984
985 ModelPanel.Invalidate();
986 }

◆ SetCurrentControl()

void BrawlCrate.UI.Model_Previewer.ModelEditControl.ModelEditControl.SetCurrentControl ( )
inline
234 {
235 Control newControl;
236 SyncTexturesToObjectList = TargetAnimType == NW4RAnimType.SRT || TargetAnimType == NW4RAnimType.PAT;
237 switch (TargetAnimType)
238 {
239 case NW4RAnimType.CHR:
240 newControl = chr0Editor;
241 break;
242 case NW4RAnimType.SHP:
243 newControl = shp0Editor;
244 break;
245 case NW4RAnimType.VIS:
246 newControl = vis0Editor;
247 break;
248 case NW4RAnimType.SCN:
249 newControl = scn0Editor;
250 break;
251 case NW4RAnimType.CLR:
252 newControl = clr0Editor;
253 break;
254 case NW4RAnimType.SRT:
255 newControl = srt0Editor;
256 break;
257 case NW4RAnimType.PAT:
258 newControl = pat0Editor;
259 break;
260 default:
261 newControl = null;
262 break;
263 }
264
265 if (_currentControl != newControl)
266 {
267 if (_currentControl != null)
268 {
269 _currentControl.Visible = false;
270 }
271
272 _currentControl = newControl;
273
274 if (!(_currentControl is SRT0Editor) && !(_currentControl is PAT0Editor))
275 {
276 SyncTexturesToObjectList = false;
277 }
278
279 if (_currentControl != null)
280 {
281 _currentControl.Visible = true;
282 }
283 }
284
285 AnimChanged();
286 CheckDimensions();
287 UpdateEditor();
288 UpdatePropDisplay();
289 }

)
inlineprivate
374 {
375 ModelPanelViewport curViewport = modelPanel.CurrentViewport;
376 ModelPanelViewport newViewport = ModelPanelViewport.DefaultPerspective;
377 newViewport.BackgroundColor = curViewport.BackgroundColor;
378 ModelPanel.AddViewport(newViewport);
379

382 float xMax = curViewport.Percentages._z;

385

387 newViewport.SetPercentages(xMin, yMin, xMax, averageY);
388
389 ModelPanel.Invalidate();
390 }
